      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "You raise a critical point that \"clean\" is rarely absolute when assessing energy sources. The ecological costs associated with mining rare earths and metals for wind turbines are substantial and must be acknowledged. However, the continuous, large-scale release of greenhouse gases from burning natural gas causes global, systemic climate damage that is vastly different from localized mining impacts. The net environmental benefit must account for this difference between localized extraction harm versus global atmospheric pollution.",
